obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46984)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Definition of stage-carriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46984&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `Every carriage drawn by one or more ^1`
  line `horses which shall`
  line `ordinarily be used for the purpose of conveying passengers for hire to or from any place in ^2[the`
  line `States] shall, without regard to the form or construction of such carriage, be deemed to be a stagecarriage within the meaning of this Act.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. All expressions and provisions in this Act applied to horses, also apply to all other animals employed in drawing stagecarriages, see section 21, infra.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the Provinces" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "British India".`
  line
  line `3. Proviso to s. 1 which read: "Provided that this Act shall not apply to carriages not ordinarily used for journey of a greater`
  line `distance than twenty miles" rep. by Act 1 of 1898, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46985)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Carriages to be licensed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46985&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `No carriage shall be used as a stage-carriage unless licensed by a`
  line `^1Magistrate or by the ^2*** Commissioner of Police of a Presidency-town.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. For definition of "Magistrate", see s. 21, infra.`
  line
  line `2. The word "Chief" rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46986)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to refuse license.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. The word Chief rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46986&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate or ^1*** Commissioner of Police to whom the`
  line `application for a license of a stage-carriage is made may refuse to license the same, if he shall be of`
  line `opinion that such stage-carriage is unserviceable or is unsafe or unfit for public accommodation or`
  line use.
  line
  line `Particulars of license.--If a Magistrate or ^1*** Commissioner of Police as aforesaid shall grant a`
  line `license, the license shall set forth the number thereof, the name and residence of the proprietor of the`
  line `stage-carriage, the place at which his head office is held, the largest number of passengers and the`
  line `greatest weight of luggage to be carried in or on such carriage, the number of horses by which such`
  line `carriage is to be drawn, and the name of the place at which such carriage is licensed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46987)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Charge for and duration of license.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46987&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[For every such license there shall be paid by the`
  line `proprietor of the stage-carriage the sum of five rupees or such less sum as the ^2[State Government] may`
  line `fix, and such license shall be in force for one year from the date thereof.]`
  line
  line `When a licensed stage-carriage is transferred to a new proprietor within the year, the name of such`
  line `new proprietor shall, on application to that effect, be substituted in the license for the name of the`
  line `former proprietor without any further payment for that year; and every person who appears by the`
  line `license to be the proprietor, shall be deemed to be such proprietor for all the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1898, s. 3, for the original paragraph.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46988)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Particulars to be painted on conspicuous part of carriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46988&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On any stage-carriage`
  line `being licensed, the proprietor thereof shall cause the number of the license and all the other particulars`
  line `of the license to be distinctly painted in the English language and character upon a conspicuous part of`
  line `such stage-carriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46989)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Penalty for letting carriage without having particulars painted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46989&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The proprietor of`
  line `any licensed stage-carriage who shall let such stage-carriage for hire without the particulars specified`
  line `in section 3 being painted on such carriage in the manner directed in the last preceding section, shall`
  line `be liable to a fine not exceeding one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46990)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Penalty for letting for hire unlicensed carriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46990&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Whoever lets for hire any stagecarriage without the same being licensed as provided by this Act, shall be liable, on a first conviction,`
  line `to a fine not exceeding one hundred rupees, and on any subsequent conviction, to a fine which may`
  line `extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47043)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Penalty for allowing carriage to be drawn by fewer animals or more passengers, etc., to be carried than provided by license.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47043&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Any proprietor, or agent of a proprietor, or any`
  line `driver of a licensed stage-carriage, who, knowingly permits such carriage to be drawn by a less`
  line `number of horses, or who knowingly permits a larger number of passengers, or a greater weight of`
  line `luggage, to be carried by such stage-carriage than shall be provided by the license, shall be liable on a`
  line `first conviction to a fine not exceeding one hundred rupees, and on any subsequent conviction, to a`
  line `fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `In every case where such stage-carriage shall be proved to have been drawn by a less number of`
  line `horses, or to have carried a larger number of passengers or a greater weight of luggage, than shall be`
  line `provided by the license, the proprietor of such carriage shall be held to have knowingly permitted`
  line `such offence, unless he shall prove that the offence was not committed with his connivance, and that`
  line `he had taken every reasonable precaution and had made reasonable provision to prevent the`
  line `commission of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46992)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Penalty for ill-treating animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46992&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Any person who shall cruelly beat, ill-treat, over-drive,`
  line `abuse, torture or cause or procure to be cruelly beaten, ill-treated, overdriven, abused or tortured, any`
  line `horse employed in drawing or harnessed to any stage-carriage, or who shall harness to or drive in any`
  line `stage-carriage any horse which from sickness, age, wounds or other cause is unfit to be driven in such`
  line `stage-carriage, shall for every such offence be liable to a fine not exceeding one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46993)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Revocation of license.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1.The word "Chief" rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46993&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any Magistrate or ^1*** Commissioner of Police within`
  line `the local limits of whose jurisdiction any stage-carriage shall ply, or who has granted the license of`
  line `any stage-carriage, may cancel the license of such stage-carriage if it shall appear to him that such`
  line `stage-carriage or any horse or any harness used with such carriage is unserviceable or unsafe or`
  line `otherwise unfit for public accommodation or use.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46994)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Penalty for not conforming to provisions of section 5.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46994&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `In any station or place in`
  line `which a Magistrate shall reside and be, any police-officer may, in any place within two miles of the`
  line `office of such Magistrate, seize any stage-carriage with the horse harnessed thereto, if the full particulars of the license of such stage-carriage be not distinctly painted on such stage-carriage in the`
  line `manner provided in section 5 of this Act.`
  line
  line `Such carriage with the horse harnessed thereto shall be taken without delay by such police-officer`
  line `before such Magistrate, who shall forthwith proceed to hear and determine the complaint of such`
  line `police-officer; and, if thereupon any fine is imposed by such Magistrate and such fine is paid, such`
  line `stage-carriage and horse shall be immediately released; and if such fine be not paid, such stage- carriage and horse may be detained for twenty days as security for the payment thereof; and if the`
  line `fine be not sooner paid, they may be sold and the proceeds applied (so far as they extend) to the`
  line `payment of the said fine, and all costs and charges incurred on account of the detention and sale;`
  line `and the surplus (if any), when claimed, shall be paid to the proprietor of such carriage and horse; and`
  line `if such surplus be not claimed within a further period of two months from such sale, the same shall be`
  line `forfeited to the State.`
  line
  line `If the proceeds of such sale do not fully pay the fine and costs and charges aforesaid, the balance`
  line `may be recovered as hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46995)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Penalty for misconduct on part of drivers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46995&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `If any driver of any stage-carriage, or any other`
  line `person having the care thereof, shall, through intoxication, neglect, or by wanton or furious driving, or`
  line `by any other misconduct, endanger the safety of any passenger or other person, or shall injure or`
  line `endanger the property of the proprietor of such stage-carriage or of any other person, every such`
  line `person so offending shall be liable to a fine not exceeding one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46996)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Penalty when recoverable from proprietor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46996&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the driver of any stage-carriage or`
  line `the owner of any horse employed in drawing any stage-carriage shall have committed any offence`
  line `against this Act for the commission whereof any penalty is by this Act imposed, other than an offence`
  line `specified in section 8, and such driver or owner shall not be known, or being known cannot be found,`
  line `or if the penalty cannot be recovered from such driver or owner, the proprietor of such carriage shall`
  line `be liable to every such penalty as if he had been the driver of such carriage or owner of such horse at`
  line `the time when such offence was committed:`
  line
  line `Proviso.--Provided that if any such proprietor shall make out, to the satisfaction of the Magistrate`
  line `before whom any complaint or information shall be heard, by sufficient evidence, that the offence was`
  line `committed by such driver or owner without the privity or knowledge of such proprietor, and that no`
  line `profit, advantage, or benefit, either directly or indirectly, has accrued or can accrue to such proprietor`
  line `therefrom, and that he has used his endeavour to find out such driver or owner, and has done all that`
  line `was in his power to recover the amount of the penalty from him, the Magistrate may discharge the`
  line `proprietor from such penalty, and shall levy the same upon such driver or owner when found.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46997)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Issue of summons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46997&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any charge is made before any Magistrate of any offence`
  line `under this Act on which it is necessary to issue a summons to the proprietor of a stage-carriage, the`
  line `Magistrate shall issue such summons directed to such proprietor or his nearest agent, and may`
  line `transmit such summons by letter-post, which shall be deemed to be good service thereof.`
  line
  line `The letter shall be registered at the post-office, and the cost of the registration shall be borne by the`
  line `Government in the first instance, but may be charged as costs in the case.`
  line
  line `The summons shall allow a reasonable time, in reference to the distance to which the summons is`
  line `sent, for the appearance of such proprietor or his agent as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46998)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. The word "Chief" rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46998&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `All penalties incurred under this Act shall be adjudged by a`
  line `Magistrate or ^1*** Commissioner of Police as aforesaid, and all orders made under this Act by such`
  line `Magistrate or^1*** Commissioner of Police shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46999)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Recovery of penalties, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=46999&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `All penalties imposed under this Act, or any balance of any fine,`
  line `costs, or charges as mentioned in section 11 of this Act, may in case of non-payment or non-recovery`
  line `thereof be levied by distress and sale of the movable property of the offender by warrant under the`
  line `hand of the Magistrate who imposed the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (47000)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Offender may be apprehended and detained in custody until return of warrant of distress.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47000&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `In case any such penalties shall not be forthwith paid, such Magistrate may order the`
  line `offender to be apprehended and detained in safe custody until the return can be conveniently made to`
  line `such warrant of distress, unless the offender shall give security to the satisfaction of such Magistrate`
  line `for his appearance at such place and time as shall be appointed for the return of the warrant of`
  line distress.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (47001)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Imprisonment of offender if distress not sufficient.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. The words "provided he is not a European British subject" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47001&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If upon the return of such warrant it`
  line `shall appear that no sufficient distress can be had whereon to levy such penalty, and the same shall not`
  line `be forthwith paid, or in case it shall appear to the satisfaction of such Magistrate by the confession of`
  line `the offender or otherwise that he has not sufficient goods and chattels whereupon such penalty could`
  line `be levied if warrant of distress were issued, such Magistrate may, by warrant under his hand, commit`
  line `the offender ^1*** to prison, there to be imprisoned, according to the discretion of such officer, for any`
  line `term not exceeding two calendar months when the amount of penalty shall not exceed fifty rupees,`
  line `and for any term not exceeding four calendar months when the amount shall not exceed one hundred`
  line `rupees, and for any term not exceeding six calendar months in any other case, the commitment to be`
  line `determinable in each of the cases aforesaid on payment of the amount.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (47002)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Recovery of penalty and costs from European British subjects.] Rep. by the A.O. 1950.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47002&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (47003)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47003&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `On complaint made before any Magistrate of any offence committed under this`
  line `Act, it shall not be necessary to prove that the offence was committed within the local limits of such`
  line `Magistrate or other officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (47004)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47004&sectionno=20A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Power to make rules.--(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes and objects of this Act in the territories under its`
  line `administration or any part of the said territories.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribe forms for licenses under this Act, the sums payable for the same and the`
  line `conditions on which they may be granted, and the cases in which they may be revoked;`
  line
  line `(b) provide for the inspection of stage-carriages, and of the animals employed in drawing them;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) regulate the number and length of the stages for which animals may be driven in stagecarriages, and the manner in which they shall be harnessed and yoked.`
  line
  line `(3) In making any rule under this section the ^2[State Government] may direct that a breach thereof`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by Act 1 of 1898, s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (47005)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47005&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The term "Magistrate" in this Act shall include all`
  line `Magistrates and other persons exercising the powers of a Magistrate:`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `Act applicable to all animals used for drawing carriages.--^2[All expressions and provisions`
  line `which in this Act are applied to horses shall also apply to all other animals employed in drawing any`
  line `carriage ordinarily used for the purpose of conveying passengers for hire to or from any place in the`
  line `States:]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The definition of "British India" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 1876, s. 1, for the third sentence of section 21.`
  line
  line `3. The definitions relating to "number" and "gender" rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (47006)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Extent of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47006&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Extent of Act. --This Act, as amended by subsequent Acts, extends to the whole of India`
  line `except ^2[the territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B`
  line `States]; but it shall not apply to carriages ordinarily plying for hire within the limits of any`
  line `municipality or cantonment or other place in which any law for the regulation of carriages is for the`
  line `time being in force. ]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sections 22 and 23 added by Act 1 of 1898, s. 5. The section 22 regarding the commencement of this Act as originally`
  line `passed had been rep. by Act 14 of 1870, s. 1 and the Schedule Part II.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for Part B States.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (47007)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to State Government to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446&sectionId=47007&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_000010_186116_1523267005446
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^1[23. Power to State Government to exempt. --The ^2[State Government] may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, exempt any carriage or class of carriages from all or any of the provisions of this`
  line Act.]
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sections 22 and 23 added by Act 1 of 1898, s. 5. The section 22 regarding the commencement of this Act as originally`
  line `passed had been rep. by Act 14 of 1870, s. 1 and the Schedule Part II.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
